						<summary>

						<p>On wall behind the sculpture of royal personage at the southern entrance of the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>A.D. 1087.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated in the Chālukya-Vikrama year 11, Naḷa, Āshāḍha Puṇṇame, Monday, lunar eclipse, Vyātipāta (Irregular).</p>						

						<p>The inscription records a gift of land for a flower-garden by the <hi rend="italic">Ūroḍeyas, etc.,</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">Brahmapuri</hi> village Kuṟuvatti after laving the feet of Abhinava Vā[ji]dēva, who seems to be an ascetic of the Kālamukha order.</p>						

						</summary>
